description.excerpt: The tvmodels library contains pretrained vision models in pytorch trained on ImageNet. Some of these models are available in torchvision but some are not, so you can load them for here.

installation.excerpt:
Run the following to install:
```python
pip install tvmodels
```

usage.excerpt:
```python
from tvmodels.models import se_resnet50, resnet18

#: Load the models
se_res_model = se_resnet50(pretrained=True)
res_model = resnet18(pretrained=True)
```
